# Top-level env (used by docker-compose).
# The ACP sidecar reads its own credentials from acp-v2/.env — see acp-v2/.env.example.

# Override the default ASP.NET environment if you want development logging in containers:
# ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT=Development

# Optional shared secret between the sidecar and the C# API. When set, the API
# requires X-API-Key on every non-/health request, and the sidecar forwards
# the same value. Leave blank to keep the boilerplate's private-network-only
# posture (no auth between containers). docker-compose's ${BASICBOT_API_KEY:-}
# substitution reads from your host shell or this file (next to docker-compose.yml).
# BASICBOT_API_KEY=
